{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:58:53.531385+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:cnBRcq | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 3b25bcaadbf40a33af1ebf5afee792282d28d196)", "id": "lc_391275cd-2788-4851-8737-414eb6f849d4"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:cnBRcq | services:\n| MCP:cnBRcq |   db:\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     image: postgres:16-alpine\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     container_name: pgdev_db\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     restart: unless-stopped\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     environment:\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       POSTGRES_USER: ${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:-app}\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       POSTGRES_DB: ${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     ports:\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - \"5432:5432\"\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     volumes:\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - ./.pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - ./config/postgresql.conf:/etc/postgresql/postgresql.conf:ro\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - ./config/pg_hba.conf:/etc/postgresql/pg_hba.conf:ro\n| MCP:cnBRcq |     command:\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - postgres\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - -c\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - config_file=/etc/postgresql/postgresql.conf\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - -c\n| MCP:cnBRcq |       - hba_file=/etc/postgresql/pg_hba.conf", "id": "lc_6ebf591b-14ca-48b0-80c4-2c299f966207"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0293a01e-1c87-4e30-8292-1186c25c2907", "tool_call_id": "call_9cc768c88f9a4a78a2d1b8fb", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:59:08.809821+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a walkthrough of the three database migrations in this repository, in the order they would be applied:\n\n---\n\n### Migration 001 — `001_create_users.sql`\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id           BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    email        TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    display_name TEXT,\n    created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n**What it does:** Creates the foundational `users` table. Each user gets an auto-incrementing `id`, a unique `email` (required), an optional `display_name`, and an automatic `created_at` timestamp.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 002 — `002_create_sessions.sql`\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n```\n**What it does:** Creates a `sessions` table for tracking user login sessions. Each session has a UUID primary key, a foreign key `user_id` referencing `users.id` with `ON DELETE CASCADE` (so deleting a user automatically removes their sessions), plus `issued_at` and `expires_at` timestamps for session lifetime management.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 003 — `003_add_session_index.sql`\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n**What it does:** Adds a B-tree index on the `user_id` column of the `sessions` table. This speeds up queries that look up sessions by user (e.g., \"find all active sessions for this user\" or \"delete all sessions for this user\").\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe migration sequence tells a simple, clean story:\n\n1. **Create the users table** — the base entity.\n2. **Create the sessions table** — depends on `users` via a foreign key.\n3. **Index the sessions table** — an optimization step after the table is in place.\n\nThe project uses **PostgreSQL 16** (per `docker-compose.yml`) and the SQL dialect confirms that (`BIGSERIAL`, `TIMESTAMPTZ`, `UUID` primary keys). There's no automated migration runner visible in the repo — the migrations appear to be applied manually or by a tool configured outside this codebase (e.g., `psql -f` or a migration library).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 529, "prompt_tokens": 5402, "total_tokens": 5931, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 15, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4864}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "bb5f7b0e25a347cfa63e275d6db5f379", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead89-8d5e-7fe3-9b11-e2b1373d28d9-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5402, "output_tokens": 529, "total_tokens": 5931, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4864}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 15}}}}]}}}
